# cursorProxy Core Context

- `cursorProxy` is an edge-compatible multi-provider AI proxy for DeepSeek, Kimi, MiniMax, Xiaomi MiMo, GLM / ZHIPU AI, and Azure Foundry.
- `api/proxy.js` is the main entrypoint and holds the provider orchestration.
- `api/models.js` handles model parsing, public/private model IDs, and provider routing.
- Azure adapters live in `api/azure-openai.js` and `api/azure-anthropic.js`.
- Kimi K2.x request sanitization lives in `api/kimi.js` (`sanitizeKimiBody`); default Kimi model is `kimi-k2.7-code`.
- GLM request sanitization lives in `api/glm.js` (`sanitizeGlmBody`); default GLM model is `glm-5.2`, default upstream is `https://open.bigmodel.cn/api/coding/paas/v4`, and global Z.AI uses `UPSTREAM_GLM=https://api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4`.
- Reasoning and cache helpers live in `api/reasoning.js`, `api/cache.js`, and `api/kv.js`.
- All `api/*.js` files are shared edge-safe modules. Do not introduce `node:*` imports or `ioredis` there.
- `server.js` is the Docker-only wrapper around the shared proxy logic.
- `vercel.json` and `cloud-functions/` provide platform routing entrypoints.
- `cliProxy` at `/home/opc/cliProxy` is the sibling reference implementation for EdgeOne Pages deployment (see `.cursor/rules/edgeone-deployment.mdc`).
- Manual verification prompts live under `.cursor/test-cases/`.
- `wiki/` is a separate git clone for the GitHub wiki. Do not commit wiki changes in the main repo.
- **Release process**: "tag and release" means TWO steps — (1) `GIT_COMMITTER_DATE="<commit-date>" git tag -a vX.Y.Z <commit> -m "vX.Y.Z"` to create an annotated tag with NO description body, using the commit's date as tagger date so tags sort chronologically on GitHub, then (2) `gh release create vX.Y.Z --notes "..."` with the full changelog/description. Tags must never carry descriptions; descriptions belong only on GitHub Releases. Push the tag and create the release in the same turn. **Version bumps** follow semver in `code-conventions.mdc` (patch = fixes/docs; minor = new provider or operator-facing feature; major = breaking).
